track_notes:
Follow the main road up and then turn sharply right up into the forest onto a rough track. Follow this track to the end and then turn sharp left and go straight up through the forest. There is no track at this stage. Exit this section of forest and continue upwards keeping the forest to your right hand side. Exit this section over a ditch and follow the signs  to the right. Next section is a steep rocky trail and at the top of the climb exit right to the summit. The path to the summit is quite boggy.
There is a logbook at the summit in a biscuit tin. Dont forget to sign in !
The summit has good mobile signal. The climb is 1.4km and took 30 mins. Its quite a rough climb, apart from the first 200m.

Heres a slightly shorter route. Instead of heading up the mountain road, just head down to the main road and then jump straight up onto the ditch and into the woods and head straight up through the forest to join the original trail.

Dont forget to sign the visitors book.
